Cell["\<\
As the data, and the questions asked about it, become more sophisticated, the \
methods for combining and analysing the information become  more \
sophisticated as well.  Throughout this course, you will learn fountational \
material used to analyse and understand quantitative systems and various \
processes to analyse them. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9005011059497604`*^9, 3.9005013323094025`*^9}, {
   3.9005018694826217`*^9, 3.9005020265586557`*^9}, {3.900502121613206*^9, 
   3.900502133642044*^9}, {3.9005021661770105`*^9, 3.900502312261631*^9}, {
   3.9005023446596184`*^9, 3.9005024516097784`*^9}, {3.9005025011406865`*^9, 
   3.9005026347257586`*^9}, {3.9005034910180397`*^9, 3.900503616163398*^9}, 
   3.901023238048326*^9},ExpressionUUID->"337ac02a-c115-4bcc-82a0-\
a032fe4aa2fa"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Notation", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5570838687674*^9, 3.5570838705614*^9}, {
  3.90050248423242*^9, 3.9005024851181335`*^9}},
 FontFamily->"Times New Roman",
 CellTags->
  "Introduction",ExpressionUUID->"d7b92486-df4f-4a05-82ee-8b304bf3df41"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Throughout the text, it is important to pay attention to what different \
letters represent. If ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["m", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "be5c12e0-3ffb-4f37-a6f3-de189688f498"],
 " and",
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "52612c63-8d98-47c1-b2a3-8a6a8a238289"],
 " are positive integers, an",
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"m", "\[Cross]", "n"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"2179e086-9fff-435b-8892-9122a336cdf2"],
 StyleBox[" matrix ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "is a rectangular array of numbers with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["m", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "abe6bbbe-3e40-4dec-ae4e-33fedd6d962c"],
 " rows and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a738ed95-9b51-4127-beab-96e3dfcbbeb5"],
 " columns. If a matrix is labeled using the capital letter ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["A", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "284ee52d-17ef-4282-9c04-ab29c191fe35"],
 ", then the number or entry in the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["i", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3fd59247-b9fd-4b89-944d-00d3d31f39a7"],
 "th row and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["j", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "da7c3436-5268-464f-961a-eb51d8697cd0"],
 "th column of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["A", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "80deae33-410d-4b76-8ede-3756e570d910"],
 " is represented as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["a",
     FontWeight->"Normal"], 
    StyleBox["ij",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ac7d6794-4da3-40f4-aebd-6643a6ffc361"],
 " and is called the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"i", ",", "j"}], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "77e30b1e-d3d9-4ede-8e32-b2551db151ea"],
 "-entry of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["A", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "29c2e975-c711-423b-b79c-80bd91d571a4"],
 ". Similarly, the number or entry in the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["i", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "537bb2b0-9dc5-4f89-abef-055a1508f124"],
 "th row and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["j", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e405bb78-89f2-46ef-adfb-467c7bf3235d"],
 "th column of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["B", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "461a56cd-da60-4dbc-9c3a-705b355d2a87"],
 " is denoted by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["b", 
    StyleBox["ij",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1f1fe592-a4ff-49c2-9daf-316a8f178c6c"],
 ", and thus the individual entries of a matrix labeled with an uppercase \
letter can be easily be identified with the corresponding lower case letter \
subscripted with the row and column determining the position of the entry.  \
The number of rows and columns of a matrix are listed as its ",
 StyleBox["size",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", with the numbers of rows listed first, followed by a \[Cross], followed \
by the number of columns. The plural of matrix is ",
 StyleBox["matrices",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.5570797393486*^9, {3.557080566626*^9, 3.5570805677024*^9}, 
   3.557083482059*^9, {3.5570835197018003`*^9, 3.5570835312302*^9}, 
   3.5570835952682*^9, 3.5570837267138*^9, {3.5570838915902*^9, 
   3.557084168459*^9}, {3.5571614013401003`*^9, 3.5571614782741003`*^9}, {
   3.5572554694011*^9, 3.5572554909135*^9}, {3.6283440947493143`*^9, 
   3.628344194535679*^9}, {3.6283442579335737`*^9, 3.62834427012169*^9}, {
   3.6283443069360867`*^9, 3.628344359485659*^9}, {3.633629240957932*^9, 
   3.633629242632827*^9}, {3.633629275381016*^9, 3.633629279284481*^9}, {
   3.634746992319767*^9, 3.6347470237715273`*^9}, {3.894534990695403*^9, 
   3.8945351406025543`*^9}, {3.8945352145449347`*^9, 
   3.8945353864839487`*^9}, {3.8945354208374033`*^9, 3.89453545065827*^9}, {
   3.894535501090457*^9, 3.894535502193654*^9}, {3.8945420064900475`*^9, 
   3.8945420765919085`*^9}, {3.894542921329832*^9, 3.8945429324010077`*^9}, {
   3.8945429672301164`*^9, 3.8945431330487733`*^9}, {3.894543519335088*^9, 
   3.8945435284276333`*^9}, {3.8946271182464066`*^9, 3.894627191626917*^9}, {
   3.894627241109977*^9, 3.8946272427154384`*^9}, {3.8946272815802774`*^9, 
